    "description": {
      "es": "",
      "en": "Wait for the Future instances (possibly created by different Executor instances) given by fs to complete. Duplicate futures given to fs are removed and will be returned only once. Returns a named 2-tuple of sets. The first set, named done, contains the futures that completed (finished or cancelled futures) before the wait completed. The second set, named not_done, contains the futures that did not complete (pending or running futures). timeout can be used to control the maximum number of seco..."
